
// This Hyperlambda code snippet appends a semicolon and a space to the existing value of the [.tail] node. It uses [set-value] to modify the [.tail] node, and [strings.concat] to concatenate the current value of [.tail] with the string "; ". The [get-value] slot retrieves the current value of [.tail] for concatenation.
set-value:x:@.tail
   strings.concat
      get-value:x:@.tail
      .:"; "
